- What's tonight?

153
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:25,620
Well, they're having
this talent show.

154
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:27,860
And I
thought I might...

155
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:30,390
- Sign up?
- Well, maybe?

156
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,760
You have to have
talent to be in a talent show.

157
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:36,730
What are you gonna do?
Shine shoes?

158
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:38,200
It's Dia de los Muertos.

159
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:41,640
No one's going anywhere.
Tonight is about family.

160
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:44,460
Ofrenda room. Vamonos.

161
00:09:55,190 --> 00:09:57,050
Don't give me that look.

162
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:59,890
Dia de los Muertos
is the one night of the year

163
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:01,930
our ancestors
can come visit us.

164
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:04,160
We've put their photos
on the ofrenda

165
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,060
so their spirits
can cross over.

166
00:10:06,070 --> 00:10:08,030
That is very important.

167
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:10,930
If we don't put them up,
they can't come.

168
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:12,670
We made all this food,

169
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:15,310
set out the things
they loved in life, mijo.

170
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:18,680
All this work
to bring the family together.

171
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:21,950
I don't want you sneaking
off to who knows where.

172
00:10:21,950 --> 00:10:23,380
Where are you going?

173
00:10:23,380 --> 00:10:24,920
I thought
we were done.

174
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:28,050
Ay, Dios mio. Being part
of this family means

175
